text: Adams and Sickles Building is located in Trenton, Mercer County, New Jersey, United States. The building was constructed in 1900 and added to the National Register of Historic Places on January 31, 1980. It was the focal point for the West End neighborhood, remembered for its soda fountain and corner druggist. ==See also== *National Register of Historic Places listings in Mercer County, New Jersey ==References== Category:Commercial buildings on the National Register of Historic Places in New Jersey Category:Queen Anne architecture in New Jersey Category:Commercial buildings completed in 1900 Category:Buildings and structures in Trenton, New Jersey Category:National Register of Historic Places in Trenton, New Jersey Category:New Jersey Register of Historic Places
